To calculate the Net Profit Margin, we use the formula:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Net Profit = 835,266.51
- Total Revenue = 2,637,011.03

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{835,266.51}{2,637,011.03} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = 0.3167 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = 31.67\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Net Profit Margin': '31.67%'} }
```
